sts/infinispan-embedded/**/*\n+     area/infra:\n+        - .github/**/*\n+        - azure-mvn-settings.xml\n+        - azure-pipelines.yml", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2ODg1MTQxMQ=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "453709f855822f3fcef1f91e4456d7914c9668a4"}, "originalPosition": 26}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2ODg1NzYyNw==", "bodyText": "I withdraw this one. If we add a something new in the native pipeline, we don't want to have area/infra otherwise it won't be properly detected as an orphan.\nIs there a way to add labels only if we haven't added any others? I'm thinking about this for infra and dependencies. They should be added if the PR doesn't touch anything else. In the case of dependencies, it's just unnecessary noise, in the case of infra, it's more annoying as issues with this label are ignored in the orphan detection.", "url": "https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/6673#discussion_r368857627", "createdAt": "2020-01-21T08:11:30Z", "author": {"login": "gsmet"}, "path": ".github/boring-cyborg.yml", "diffHunk": "@@ -119,6 +124,10 @@ labelPRBasedOnFilePath:\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-cache-jpa/**/*\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-client/**/*\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-embedded/**/*\n+     area/infra:\n+        - .github/**/*\n+        - azure-mvn-settings.xml\n+        - azure-pipelines.yml", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2ODg1MTQxMQ=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "453709f855822f3fcef1f91e4456d7914c9668a4"}, "originalPosition": 26}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2ODk4NDY1Mw==", "bodyText": "at the moment we can't tweak the label add logic.\nFor dependencies - why wouldn't you want that added whenever the bom.xml is modified ?\nWhat is it you are concretely looking for in your orphan deteection ? Maybe we want to add a separate label for that and leave area/infra as what is used to be able to find pullrequests that relates to a specific area ? (That\u2019s what I'm after - being able to setup a query  that lists the areas i'm interested in being aware of - area/infra and dependencies being one no matter if its happening together with 0 or many other changes)", "url": "https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/6673#discussion_r368984653", "createdAt": "2020-01-21T12:58:15Z", "author": {"login": "maxandersen"}, "path": ".github/boring-cyborg.yml", "diffHunk": "@@ -119,6 +124,10 @@ labelPRBasedOnFilePath:\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-cache-jpa/**/*\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-client/**/*\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-embedded/**/*\n+     area/infra:\n+        - .github/**/*\n+        - azure-mvn-settings.xml\n+        - azure-pipelines.yml", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2ODg1MTQxMQ=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "453709f855822f3fcef1f91e4456d7914c9668a4"}, "originalPosition": 26}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3MDIyODU3Nw==", "bodyText": "area/infra has been specifically added for the orphan detection. Everything having this label is ignored as it's about the infra and not about Quarkus itself.", "url": "https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/6673#discussion_r370228577", "createdAt": "2020-01-23T16:38:18Z", "author": {"login": "gsmet"}, "path": ".github/boring-cyborg.yml", "diffHunk": "@@ -119,6 +124,10 @@ labelPRBasedOnFilePath:\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-cache-jpa/**/*\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-client/**/*\n         - integration-tests/infinispan-embedded/**/*\n+     area/infra:\n+        - .github/**/*\n+        - azure-mvn-settings.xml\n+        - azure-pipelines.yml", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM2ODg1MTQxMQ=="}, "originalCommit": {"oid": "453709f855822f3fcef1f91e4456d7914c9668a4"}, "originalPosition": 26}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDM3MDM5NDI5